# WCMA Social Media Monitor — Prerequisites

## Meta / Facebook Side

1. **Meta Business Account** — test account or WCMA's existing one in dev mode
2. **Test Facebook Page** — "WCMA Dev Test Page" under the business account, isolated from real WCMA page
3. **Meta Developer App** — type "Business", with "Facebook Login" and "Webhooks" products added, at https://developers.facebook.com/
4. **App Roles & Test Users** — developer/tester accounts added as app roles; Meta Test Users created via App Dashboard → Roles → Test Users
5. **Page Access Token (Long-Lived)** — generated by a user with MODERATE+ role on the test page; short-lived exchanged for long-lived (~60 days)

## Required Facebook Permissions

| Permission | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `pages_read_engagement` | Read comments on page posts |
| `pages_read_user_content` | Read user-generated content |
| `pages_manage_metadata` | Subscribe to webhooks |
| `pages_show_list` | List pages the app is installed on |

## Infrastructure Side

6. **Webhook Endpoint** — dev: `ngrok` tunnel to localhost; prod: cloud VM or serverless function; must be HTTPS with valid TLS cert
7. **Sentiment API Key** — OpenAI API key or alternative LLM provider
8. **Email Credentials** — SMTP (Gmail app password / Outlook / WCMA mail server) or API key for SendGrid/Mailgun
9. **Python Environment** — Python 3.10+, virtual environment, core deps: `requests`, `flask` or `fastapi`, `openai`, email libs

## Setup Order

Items 1–5 first (Meta side), then 6–9 (infra side). App Review submission needed only when moving from dev to live mode.